observations.recommendation:
1. Confirm the amount of the payables from the list of the identified creditors to determine which of the payables are still valid and bonafide obligation;
2. Drop from the books of accounts the undocumented obligations/ payables;
3. Make necessary adjustments in the books of accounts if proven to be without existing creditors for an accurate presentation of the payable account in the Financial Statements.

Identify specifically the developmental projects to be funded under the 20% Development Fund before the approval of the AIP so that only specific priority projects will be funded and to ensure measurement of performance of the Municipality relative to the implementation of its developmental projects;
Require the Municipal Planning and Development Office to ensure that projects to be implemented from the 20% Development Fund should be specific as to details such as, but not limited to Project Name, Project Location, Schedule Time Frame, Bill of Materials, Program of Works, and other necessary documents needed.
Fast track and prioritize the full implementation of the development projects as embodied in the Local Development Plan in pursuance of the law and ensure that allocated funds are timely and optimally utilized for projects identified in accordance with existing guidelines.
